          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Cincinnati Ohio</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <date>21<hi rend="sup">st</hi> Novr 1848</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>Reverend Sir.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">I this day received your favor of the
                                                  <date>16th</date><lb/> and immediately
                                        communicated to <persName>Mr Gutheime</persName> the portion
                                        of it<lb/> relating to him: He intends writing you. It is
                                        painful to<lb/> learn that labours such as you have put
                                        forth on behalf of our<lb/> faith has hitherto not been
                                        better rewarded in a pecuniary sense<lb/> you will however
                                        always the satisfaction of feeling that you have<lb/> done
                                        your duty and be persevering in it you will I trust
                                        eventually<lb/> succeed in rousing our people and reaping a
                                        just reward for your<lb/> exertions. On the appearance in
                                        the occident for <date>December</date><lb/> of your article
                                        and that of <persName>Dr Wise</persName> on the subject of
                                        ministers holding<lb/> a meeting, I will pay particular
                                        attention to them: I thank you for<lb/> the offer to insert,
                                        in the number for <date>January</date> any ideas I may wish
                                        to<lb/> publish on the subject but persuaded as I am that it
                                        will be far<lb/> better treated by you and <persName>Dr
                                                  Wise</persName> I will not risk injuring the
                                        cause<lb/> I have so much at heart to promote by any
                                        observations of mine<lb/> upon it. You have not I think
                                        fully understood me on the<lb/> subject of calling attention
                                        to my little work “a Retrospect &amp;c”<lb/> I beg therefore
                                        to explain—The points treated in it though little<lb/>
                                        familiar to our people generally are still most important to
                                        them<lb/> to be informed upon. Those points I need not
                                        indicate to one of<lb/> your rending<add>?</add> and
                                        knowledge: It would ill become me to review<lb/> my own
                                        work, more especially as it is in the hands of one so<lb/>
                                        much more competent to do it, and would you resolve to
                                        under<lb/> take it</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>I venture to predict the articles you might occasionally<lb/>
                                        insert in the occident elucidating the points in
                                        question<lb/> would not be considered the least interesting
                                        in it.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Will you thank <persName>Mr. Sibreuce</persName>
                                        for the message<lb/> conveyed to me through you &amp;
                                        believe me</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Revd Sir Yours sincerely</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">
                                        <persName role="author">A A. Lindo</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
